# Adding Refresh Control

FlatList (and SectionList) have built‑in pull‑to‑refresh support via two props:

* `refreshing` – a boolean indicating if a refresh is in progress.
* `onRefresh` – a function called when the user pulls down.

```jsx
const [refreshing, setRefreshing] = useState(false);

const handleRefresh = async () => {
  setRefreshing(true);
  await fetchNewData();
  setRefreshing(false);
};

<FlatList
  data={data}
  renderItem={...}
  refreshing={refreshing}
  onRefresh={handleRefresh}
/>
```

Load more data when the user scrolls near the end using `onEndReached`.

```jsx
const [data, setData] = useState([]);
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
const [page, setPage] = useState(1);

const loadMore = async () => {
  if (loading) return;
  setLoading(true);
  const newData = await fetchPage(page);
  setData(prev => [...prev, ...newData]);
  setPage(p => p + 1);
  setLoading(false);
};

<FlatList
  data={data}
  renderItem={...}
  onEndReached={loadMore}
  onEndReachedThreshold={0.5} // when 50% from the bottom
  ListFooterComponent={loading && <Text>Loading...</Text>}
/>
```
